returns.series: the address of the otoken created

returns._0: the value of the reactor in the liquidity pool asset

params.delta: The exposure of the liquidity pool that the reactor needs to hedge against

returns._0: deltaChange The difference in delta exposure as a result of strategy execution

params.newOptionExchange: the option exchange to migrate to

params._operationProcedures: an array of actions to be executed sequentially

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

params._series: the list of series to redeem

returns._0: the amount actually withdrawn from the reactor denominated in the liquidity pool asset

addressbook().notice: address book used for the gamma protocol

approvedCollateral(address,bool).notice: mapping of approved collateral for puts and calls

changeApprovedCollateral(address,bool,bo.notice: set whether a collateral is approved for selling to the vault

createOtoken((uint64,uint128,bool,addres.notice: create an otoken, distinguished from issue because we may not want this option on the option registry

formatStrikePrice(uint256,address).notice: Converts strike price to 1e8 format and floors least significant digits if needed

getDelta().notice: Returns the delta exposure of the reactor

getPoolDenominatedValue().notice: Returns the value of the reactor denominated in the liquidity pool asset

getPortfolioValuesFeed().notice: get the portfolio values feed used by the liquidity pool

hedgeDelta(int256).notice: Execute a strategy to hedge delta exposure

maxTradeSize().notice: maximum amount allowed for a single trade

migrateOtokens(address,address[]).notice: migrate otokens held by this address to a new option exchange

minTradeSize().notice: minimum amount allowed for a single trade

operate((uint8,(uint256,address,address,.notice: entry point to the contract for users, takes a queue of actions for both opyn and rysk and executes them sequentially

poolFees(address).notice: pool fees for different swappable assets

redeem(address[]).notice: get the dhv to redeem an expired otoken

setPoolFee(address,uint24).notice: set the uniswap v3 pool fee for a given asset, also give the asset max approval on the uni v3 swap router

setTradeSizeLimits(uint256,uint256).notice: set the maximum and minimum trade size

swapRouter().notice: instance of the uniswap V3 router interface

update().notice: Handle events such as collateralisation rebalancing

withdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraw a given asset from the hedging reactor to the calling liquidity pool.
